{
  "id": "vulnscan-pipeline",
  "name": "VulnScan Pipeline",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Two entry points, one pipeline\n\n- **Webhook Trigger**: called by the Backend (`POST /targets/{id}/pipeline`). This is the production path — the Backend already created the `Scan` row and passes `scan_id`/`target_id`/`host` directly in the body.\n- **Form Trigger**: open this node's \"Test URL\" in a browser to run the whole pipeline by hand (type a `target_id`, no Backend/frontend call needed). Used for demos before Módulo 8 (frontend) exists.\n\nBoth branches converge at **Resolve Pipeline Context**, which is the only node that has to know which trigger actually fired. Everything after it is a single linear chain.",
        "height": 320,
        "width": 460
      },
      "id": "note-triggers",
      "name": "Sticky Note - Triggers",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-620, -320]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Recon -> tool selection\n\nNmap runs first and unscoped (no port needed). **Select HTTP Port** reads Nmap's own response directly (not the DB) and picks the first open port that looks like HTTP(S) — this is the \"selección inteligente de herramientas\" stage from the architecture doc, kept intentionally simple. If Nmap found no open ports at all, this node returns zero items, which stops every downstream node automatically — no explicit IF/skip logic needed.",
        "height": 260,
        "width": 460
      },
      "id": "note-recon",
      "name": "Sticky Note - Recon",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [280, -320]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Web scanning (sequential)\n\nWhatWeb, Nikto, Nuclei and ZAP run one after another rather than in parallel branches — the workflow graph stays a single linear chain (easy to read/debug in the editor), and ZAP's active scan alone (3-5 min) dominates total runtime regardless of whether the other three run before or after it. Running them concurrently is a reasonable future enhancement, not a correctness requirement.\n\nEach tool's raw result is posted straight through to the Backend's `/scans/{id}/tasks` endpoint (Módulo 5) unchanged — that endpoint's ingest schema mirrors the Scanner Service's response on purpose, so there's no reshaping here.",
        "height": 280,
        "width": 700
      },
      "id": "note-scanning",
      "name": "Sticky Note - Scanning",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [1140, -320]
    },
